  "response": "No, not all sex is rape. Rape is a specific type of sexual activity that involves non-consensual penetration or sexual assault. Consensual sex, on the other hand, is when all parties involved willingly agree to engage in sexual activity. Consent is a crucial factor that differentiates consensual sex from rape. It's important for all sexual activities to be based on clear, enthusiastic, and ongoing consent from all parties involved.",
